A homeless man managed to sleep in a Cambridge University library for six weeks before staff noticed he was not a student.

The interloper took advantage of the 24-hour library at St John's College by 'tailgating' students entering the building for late-night study sessions before pretending to peruse books.

But he was rumbled after some noticed he never changed his clothes, was pretending to read books and often fell asleep and began snoring.

