University authorities were alerted and he was ordered to leave by a porter after he could not prove he was a student.

One member of the college said on Twitter the man had been 'living under the radar' for six weeks but has not been seen since.

It is believed the man was homeless and simply seeking a warm place to spend the night.

The front door of St John's Working Library is unlocked when staffed, but locked outside these hours.

However students can get in and out of the library 24-hours a day, seven days a week, using their access card.

